"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code does not correctly use the library Matplotlib. The DateFormatter and MonthLocator are used incorrectly as they are not being used in conjunction with a DateLocator. The DateFormatter will format all dates, but the MonthLocator will only locate the first day of each month. This can cause the dates in the plot to be incorrectly labeled.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19c19\\n<ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(MonthLocator())\\n---\\n>ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(MonthLocator(interval=1))\\n20c20\\n<ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%Y-%m'))\\n---\\n>ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d'))\"\n}"